

	 
      think of that one person in your life who you unconditionally care about. your best friend, perhaps, or a treasured family member.   that person, he or she,is on the verge of death. it could be an hour, it could be a day. but he's going to die before the sun rises twice. you have little more than an hour before she's out of your life.  what do you say to that person? these are the last words he'll ever hear you speak. the last chance to try and express what she has meant to you. in several moments you have to sum up an incredible span of emotion, of friendship, of love, while knowing you are never again going to see this person outside of a coffin.  what do you say? 
     
    
